## Prerequisites

- Node.js v16+
- MongoDB v5+ (local) or a MongoDB Atlas URI
- npm v8+

---

## Installation

```bash
cd backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your values
```

---

## Environment Variables

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in the values:

```env
PORT=5000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/crm_plus
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_in_production
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000
NODE_ENV=development
```

| Variable | Description | Required | Default |
|----------|-------------|----------|---------|
| `PORT` | Server port | No | `5000` |
| `MONGODB_URI` | MongoDB connection string | **Yes** | — |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secret key for signing JWTs | **Yes** | — |
| `JWT_EXPIRES_IN` | Token expiry duration | No | `7d` |
| `CLIENT_URL` | Frontend URL (CORS origin) | No | `http://localhost:3000` |
| `NODE_ENV` | Runtime environment | No | `development` |

---

## How to Run

```bash
# Development (auto-reload via nodemon)
npm run dev

# Production
npm start

# Seed database
npm run seed
```

Server runs on **http://localhost:5000**

---

## Seed Sample Data

```bash
npm run seed
```

> ⚠️ This **clears all existing data** before seeding.

Creates the following users and 20 sample leads:

| Email | Password | Role |
|-------|----------|------|
| admin@crm.com | password123 | admin |
| manager@crm.com | password123 | manager |
| sales1@crm.com | password123 | sales |
| sales2@crm.com | password123 | sales |

