## Project Structure

```
backend/
├── config/
│   ├── db.js                    # MongoDB connection via Mongoose
│   └── rbac.js                  # Permissions map (role → permission scopes)
├── controllers/
│   ├── authController.js        # register, login, logout
│   ├── leadController.js        # CRUD + stats aggregation
│   ├── notificationController.js # list, mark-read, mark-all-read
│   └── userController.js        # list users, update role
├── middlewares/
│   ├── auth.js                  # JWT verification — attaches req.user
│   ├── rbac.js                  # authorize(permission) + restrictTo(...roles)
│   ├── validate.js              # Input validation (lead fields, registration)
│   └── errorHandler.js          # Global error handler
├── models/
│   ├── Lead.js                  # Lead schema with all indexes defined
│   ├── Notification.js          # Notification schema
│   └── User.js                  # User schema with bcrypt pre-save hook
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.js                  # /auth/register, /auth/login, /auth/logout
│   ├── leads.js                 # /leads CRUD + /leads/stats/summary
│   ├── notifications.js         # /notifications list + mark-read
│   └── users.js                 # /users list + role update
├── services/
│   └── notificationService.js   # Persist to DB + emit via Socket.IO
├── utils/
│   └── seed.js                  # Database seeder script
├── .env.example
├── package.json
└── server.js                    # Express app + HTTP server + Socket.IO init
```

---

## RBAC Design

RBAC is enforced via the `authorize(permission)` middleware. Each route declares the required permission scope — not a role check — keeping permissions decoupled from roles.

```js
router.get('/',       authenticate, authorize('lead:read'),   getLeads);
router.post('/',      authenticate, authorize('lead:write'),  createLead);
router.delete('/:id', authenticate, authorize('lead:delete'), deleteLead);
```

### Roles

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `admin` | Full access to all resources including user management |
| `manager` | All leads + dashboard; can assign leads; no user management |
| `sales` | Own/assigned leads only; no dashboard |

### Permissions Matrix

| Permission | admin | manager | sales |
|------------|-------|---------|-------|
| `lead:read` | ✅ All | ✅ All | ✅ Own/assigned only |
| `lead:write` | ✅ All | ✅ All | ✅ Own/assigned only |
| `lead:delete` | ✅ Any | ❌ | ✅ Creator only |
| `user:read` | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| `user:write` | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| `dashboard:read` | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| `notification:read` | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Own only |

### Ownership Rules (enforced in controllers)

A **sales** user can access a lead only if:
- `createdBy === userId` — they created the lead, **OR**
- `assignedTo === userId` — the lead is assigned to them

**Manager/Admin** can access all leads without restriction.

---

## API Documentation

**Base URL:** `http://localhost:5000`

Protected routes require:
```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

Error response format:
```json
{ "message": "string", "errors": ["optional array"] }
```

---

### Auth

#### `POST /auth/register`

Register a new user. Defaults to `sales` role.

**Body:**
```json
{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}
```

**Response `201`:**
```json
{
  "message": "User registered successfully.",
  "user": { "id": "...", "name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com", "role": "sales" }
}
```

**Validation errors `400`:**
- name: 2–100 characters required
- email: valid format required
- password: minimum 6 characters

---

#### `POST /auth/login`

> ⚠️ Rate limited: **10 requests per 15 minutes** per IP.

**Body:**
```json
{ "email": "admin@crm.com", "password": "password123" }
```

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "token": "<jwt>",
  "user": { "id": "...", "name": "Admin User", "email": "admin@crm.com", "role": "admin" }
}
```

JWT payload includes: `sub` (userId), `role`, `iat`, `exp`

---

#### `POST /auth/logout` 🔒

**Response `200`:**
```json
{ "message": "Logged out successfully. Please delete your token on the client." }
```

---

### Leads

#### `GET /leads` 🔒 `lead:read`

Advanced paginated list using MongoDB `$facet` aggregation (data + total count in one query).

**Query Parameters:**

| Parameter | Type | Description | Default |
|-----------|------|-------------|---------|
| `q` | string | Search in name, email, phone (case-insensitive) | — |
| `status` | enum | `new` \| `contacted` \| `qualified` \| `won` \| `lost` | — |
| `source` | enum | `website` \| `referral` \| `cold` \| `social` \| `other` | — |
| `assignedTo` | ObjectId | Filter by assigned user *(manager/admin only)* | — |
| `createdFrom` | ISO date | Leads created on or after this date | — |
| `createdTo` | ISO date | Leads created on or before this date | — |
| `sort` | `field:order` | Fields: `name`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `status`, `source` | `createdAt:desc` |
| `page` | number | Page number (min: 1) | `1` |
| `limit` | number | Items per page (max: 100) | `10` |

All filters use **AND logic**. Total always reflects filters.

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "data": [ ...leads ],
  "pagination": { "page": 1, "limit": 10, "total": 45, "totalPages": 5 }
}
```

**Edge cases handled:** invalid page/limit values, invalid date format, invalid sort field/order.

---

#### `POST /leads` 🔒 `lead:write`

**Body:**
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "phone": "+91 98765 43210",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "source": "website",
  "status": "new",
  "notes": "Interested in enterprise plan",
  "assignedTo": "<userId>"
}
```

> `assignedTo` only accepted from manager/admin roles.

**Response `201`:**
```json
{ "message": "Lead created successfully.", "lead": { ...populatedLead } }
```

---

#### `GET /leads/stats/summary` 🔒 `dashboard:read`

Analytics via single `$facet` aggregation pipeline.

**Query Parameters:** `createdFrom`, `createdTo` (optional ISO dates)

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "totalLeads": 150,
  "byStatus": { "new": 45, "contacted": 30, "qualified": 25, "won": 35, "lost": 15 },
  "bySource": { "website": 80, "referral": 45, "cold": 25, "social": 10, "other": 15 }
}
```

> All enum values always present — categories with no data return `0`.

---

#### `GET /leads/:id` 🔒 `lead:read`

**Response `200`:** `{ "lead": { ...populatedLead } }`

Returns `403` if a sales user tries to access a lead they don't own or aren't assigned to.

---

#### `PATCH /leads/:id` 🔒 `lead:write`

Update any combination of fields. Only manager/admin can update `assignedTo`.

**Response `200`:** `{ "message": "Lead updated successfully.", "lead": { ...lead } }`

---

#### `DELETE /leads/:id` 🔒 `lead:delete`

**Response `200`:** `{ "message": "Lead deleted successfully." }`

Sales users can only delete leads they created.

---

### Users

#### `GET /users` 🔒 `user:read` · admin only

**Response `200`:** `{ "users": [ ...users ] }` (passwords excluded)

---

#### `GET /users/me` 🔒

Returns the currently authenticated user.

---

#### `PATCH /users/:id/role` 🔒 `user:write` · admin only

**Body:** `{ "role": "admin" | "manager" | "sales" }`

**Response `200`:** `{ "message": "User role updated successfully.", "user": { ...user } }`

---

### Notifications

#### `GET /notifications` 🔒 `notification:read`

**Query Parameters:** `page` (default 1), `limit` (default 20, max 100)

**Response `200`:**
```json
{
  "data": [ ...notifications ],
  "unreadCount": 5,
  "pagination": { "page": 1, "limit": 20, "total": 30, "totalPages": 2 }
}
```

---

#### `PATCH /notifications/read-all` 🔒 `notification:read`

Marks all of the current user's notifications as read.

---

#### `PATCH /notifications/:id/read` 🔒 `notification:read`

Marks a single notification as read (recipient-scoped).

---

### HTTP Status Codes

| Code | When returned |
|------|---------------|
| `200` | Successful GET / PATCH |
| `201` | Successful POST |
| `400` | Validation failure / bad request |
| `401` | Missing, expired, or invalid JWT |
| `403` | Valid token but insufficient permissions |
| `404` | Resource not found |
| `409` | Email already in use |
| `429` | Login rate limit exceeded |
| `500` | Unexpected server error |

---

## Real-time Notifications

Socket.IO shares the same HTTP server as Express (no separate port needed).

### How it works

1. Client connects and authenticates via JWT in the handshake
2. Server verifies the token and joins the socket to a **user-specific room** (keyed by `userId`)
3. When a trigger event fires, the notification is:
   - **Persisted to MongoDB first** — ensures no data loss if the user is offline
   - **Emitted to the user's room** via `io.to(userId).emit('notification', data)`

### Notification Triggers

| Trigger | Type | Recipients |
|---------|------|------------|
| Lead created | `lead_created` | All managers + admins (+ assigned user if set) |
| Lead assigned/reassigned | `lead_assigned` | The newly assigned user |
| Lead status changed | `lead_status_changed` | Assigned user + all managers/admins |
| Lead deleted | `lead_deleted` | All managers + admins |

### Socket Authentication

```js
// Server-side (server.js)
io.use((socket, next) => {
  const token = socket.handshake.auth?.token;
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
  socket.userId = decoded.sub;
  next();
});

io.on('connection', (socket) => {
  socket.join(socket.userId); // join personal room
});
```

---

## MongoDB Indexes

Defined directly on the Mongoose schemas in `models/Lead.js` and `models/Notification.js`:

```js
// Lead Collection
{ createdBy: 1 }                              // ownership lookups for sales RBAC
{ assignedTo: 1 }                             // assignment lookups + assignedTo filter
{ status: 1 }                                 // status filter
{ source: 1 }                                 // source filter
{ createdAt: -1 }                             // default sort (newest first)
{ status: 1, source: 1, createdAt: -1 }       // compound — common multi-filter + sort
{ createdBy: 1, assignedTo: 1, status: 1 }    // compound — RBAC + filter combo
{ name: 'text', email: 'text', phone: 'text'} // text search across 3 fields

// Notification Collection
{ recipient: 1, isRead: 1, createdAt: -1 }    // per-user list with unread filter + sort
```

---

## Design Decisions

1. **`$facet` aggregation for `GET /leads`** — retrieves data AND total count in a single MongoDB round-trip instead of two separate queries.

2. **Secondary `_id` sort** — applied alongside every lead sort to guarantee stable, predictable pagination when sort field values are identical across documents.

3. **Permission-based RBAC (not role-based)** — `authorize('lead:write')` instead of `isAdmin()`. Adding a new role only requires a change in `config/rbac.js`, not in route files.

4. **Notification persistence before emit** — saving to MongoDB before the Socket.IO emit ensures data is not lost if the client is offline or disconnects mid-delivery.

5. **Rate limiting on login** — 10 requests per 15-minute window per IP using `express-rate-limit` to prevent brute-force attacks.

6. **Normalised stats output** — all status and source enum values always appear in the analytics response with a `0` fallback, making frontend rendering predictable without null checks.